Troubleshooting Tips
Pi-hole not blocking queries:

Verify DNS is set to Pi-hole IP: docker exec pihole pihole status
Check gravity database: docker exec pihole pihole -g
Review logs: docker-compose logs pihole
ELK stack connection issues:

Check Elasticsearch health: curl localhost:9200/_cluster/health
Verify Logstash pipeline: docker-compose -f elk-docker-compose.yml logs logstash
Ensure proper file permissions on data directories
Dashboard not displaying data:

Verify Elasticsearch has data: curl localhost:9200/pihole-logs-*/_count
Check Python dependencies are installed
Review browser console for JavaScript errors
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated deploying a DNS sinkhole using Pi-hole, integrating it with ELK stack for log analysis, and building custom monitoring tools. DNS sinkholes are effective for blocking malicious domains at the network level, providing an additional layer of security. The monitoring dashboard and traffic analysis tools enable security teams to identify threats and analyze attack patterns. Continue exploring by adding more threat intelligence feeds, implementing automated response actions, and integrating with SIEM systems for comprehensive security monitoring.
